<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        FerrisPass runs under Hardened Runtime (required for Apple
        notarization) but uses no behaviors that would be restricted by it:
        - Network access works without entitlement when unsandboxed.
        - File access via NSOpenPanel/NSSavePanel is user-mediated.
        - Keychain access via the `keyring` crate uses Security framework
          and prompts the user at runtime.
        - No JIT, no unsigned dylibs, no DYLD env-var injection.

        If a future feature requires opting into a restricted behavior
        (e.g. JIT, library validation bypass), add it here as the minimal
        scope needed and document the reason.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
